title: Route OpenAI Codex models through ChatGPT subscription runtime
---
## Requirements

- Add runtime support for `openai-codex/*` or equivalent Codex subscription model targets.
- Route Codex requests to the ChatGPT Codex backend instead of the normal OpenAI-compatible `/v1` API path.
- Build authorization headers from refreshed OAuth access tokens and include `ChatGPT-Account-Id` when present.
- Keep existing OpenAI-compatible API-key flows unchanged.
- Ensure streaming and non-streaming flows both work, or return a clear temporary limitation if one mode must be staged.

## Acceptance Criteria

- A configured Codex subscription provider can be selected for Codex-targeted models without an API key.
- Requests use the ChatGPT Codex backend with bearer access token auth.
- Account-id headers are sent when available.
- Existing OpenAI-compatible provider tests remain green.
